SOCIAL media was abuzz when news broke on Tuesday that two paramedics had rescued a dumped baby. The two had knocked off in Tshwane when they saw a bag on the side of the road and stopped to investigate. They were shocked when they heard crying coming from the bag. When they looked inside, they found a baby wrapped in a blanket. They immediately checked that the child was safe and healthy before taking the baby to the nearest hospital. Life Star 911 wrote on Facebook that the two paramedics were Mike Mabasa and Jacob Motshabi. Daily Sun tried to reach them and the ambulance service without success. Smangele Thabethe wrote on Facebook: “God bless you, guys. You did what you do best. Continue saving lives.” Ditebogo Melon Chauke: “Thank you guys for saving the baby. May God protect and bless you.”